**[1845, 10-31] Ms.A.9.2.21.79**

Haughton to MWC. Says he admires the American abolitionists because they
face opposition and persecution that British abolitionists do not. “…
our agitation brings no opprobrium on our heads, quite the contrary. No
one would dare to speak against us. Our Public opinion is in favor of
liberty for all, so that you will see, instead of your drinking
exhiliration [sic] from the little fountain of our benevolence, it is we
who imbibe it largely from your flowing streams.”


